Q. (Indiscernible)?
COACH JON COOPER: I don't know.  I don't know if there's an art to it.  We've just been on both sides of it.  I can point out scenarios in the New Jersey series, definitely scenarios in the Boston series where, you know, you earn your breaks and things go your way, and you take advantage of that.  Then the other side of things is what's happened to us the first two games where I'm not so sure we've earned our breaks the way we did in the previous two series.
When you don't do that, sometimes bad things happen.  So you just have to regroup and that's it, and figure out why things haven't gone your way.  But I know we can do that.  We're doing some things in the series that we just didn't do in the playoffs.  Partially some of that is attributed to Washington's play, but a lot of it's our play too.
