COACH JON COOPER: It's hard to explain.  If we could, maybe we wouldn't be down 0-2.  But it's quick.  It goes fast, it's within 48 hours.  You know, the series is two games over and we're on the wrong side of that.  So the teams that have played (Indiscernible) over the last month we've done well getting ourselves to the Final Four.  Haven't had a good last 48 hours and we need to fix that.
Q. (Indiscernible)?
COACH JON COOPER: Yeah, the one thing is emotions are so high and so low.  The way things were going so well for us, one of the big things is don't jump on the cloud nine and sit here and say, oh, well, I thought we did a great job with that.  So now that we're not on cloud nine, it's like, well, don't feel sorry for ourselves.  It's just the opposite effect.  We're okay.  There is a reason we're here.  We've done well with that all year, so I'm not too concerned about that.  We just have to stay the course.  Don't let every little thing bother you, and you'll be okay.
